<p class="qtext_para" style="margin-bottom: 1em; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, Times, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; font-size: 15px;"><b><i>Five bang on psychological facts:-</i></b></p><ol style="margin-right: 2em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, Times, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; font-size: 15px;"><li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.7em; position: relative; left: 2em;">Tell people your own story first. They will share theirs eventually. (<b><i>The Art of Making Someone Confess</i></b>)</li><li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.7em; position: relative; left: 2em;">Tell people your deepest secrets while looking in their eyes. They will feel an instant attraction. (<b><i>The Science of Attraction</i></b>)</li><li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.7em; position: relative; left: 2em;">Interrupt someone while he narrates you a story. Ask for minute details. If a flaw is observed, then, he is weaving a lie. (<b><i>The Art of Spotting a Liar</i></b>)</li><li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.7em; position: relative; left: 2em;">Truth is always partial. You will always know it up to a certain level. None tells you the complete story. (<b><i>Truth Vs The Truth</i></b>)</li><li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; position: relative; left: 2em;">The only way to avoid abuse is to become the abuser! (<b><i>The Psychology of Abuse &amp; Cheating!</i></b>)</li></ol><p style="text-align: center; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; position: relative; left: 2em;"><a href="https://www.quora.com/What-are-some-psychological-facts-that-people-dont-know-1/answer/Dibakar-Dutta-5?srid=uLaia" target="_blank">Reference Link</a></p>
